parameter 1: The Dutch version edits lip-sync so they can translate the English dialogue into Dutch.
parameter 2: For the Danish R2 DVD release in 2004 a few songs were re-recorded due to copyright reasons, including 'Ry Cooder' (qv)'s theme from _Paris, Texas (1984)_ (qv). 'Michael Wikke' (qv) and 'Steen Rasmussen' (qv) also had to redo their voices in a those scenes. A short featurette (entitled 'Tilbage til Tonny & Sonny') featured on the DVD shows the dubbing process.
parameter 3: The original 5 episodes were re-edited in 2004 into 8 episodes which were broadcasted as weekly segments in _"Motormagasinet" (2004)_ (qv).
parameter 4: There is a slightly different edited version appearing in the 30th Episode Spe-tacular.
parameter 5: The 4Kids version included a complete replacement of the intro and outro score of the series, as well as removing suggestive content and changing the fate of several characters, as well as editing the story to be much lighter and kid friendly in tone for the US release. Such edits as removal of written Japanese characters or certain English words on various signs, billboards,etc.; cigar or anything that's a tobacco product, alcoholic like beverages, and any scenes that seem too violent. The character info cards shown in between the episodes were completely removed in English dub.
